{"questionId":"9074869","questionHtml":"<div class=\"qb-parent-stem\"><p>A string of length 0.80 m is fixed at both ends. The diagram shows a standing wave formed&nbsp;on the string. P and Q are two particles on the string.</p>\n<p style=\"text-align:center;\"><img src=\"__IMG__/83bf51f2722407be962d76a8554e1983b3c11cb6.png\"></p></div>\n<div class=\"qb-parent-stem\"><p>The variation with time&nbsp;<em>t</em>&nbsp;of the displacement of particle P is shown.</p>\n<p><img src=\"__IMG__/36a4f071734b2c8632c2df1dffac7f1db1198093.png\"></p></div>\n<div class=\"qb-leaf-prompt\"><p>Calculate the speed of waves on the string.</p></div>","markschemeHtml":"<p>wavelength <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mo>=</mo><mfrac><mn>2</mn><mn>3</mn></mfrac><mo>×</mo><mn>0</mn><mo>.</mo><mn>80</mn><mo>=</mo><mn>0</mn><mo>.</mo><mn>53</mn></math> «m» ✓</p>\n<p>speed <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mo>=</mo><mfrac><mrow><mn>0</mn><mo>.</mo><mn>53</mn></mrow><mrow><mn>2</mn><mo>.</mo><mn>8</mn><mo>×</mo><msup><mn>10</mn><mrow><mo>-</mo><mn>3</mn></mrow></msup></mrow></mfrac><mo>=</mo><mn>190</mn></math> «m s<sup>−1</sup>»&nbsp;✓</p>\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n<p><em>Allow <strong>ECF</strong> from incorrect wavelength.</em></p>","meta":{"questionId":"9074869","referenceCode":"22N.2.HL.TZ0.a.ii","subjectId":"46-dp-physics-last-assessment-2024","title":"Calculate the speed of waves on the string.","paper":"2","level":"HL","questionNumber":"a.ii","marksAvailable":"[Maximum mark: 2]","breadcrumbLabels":["Core","Core","Topic 4: Waves","4.2 – Travelling waves","Core","Topic 4: Waves"],"memberSectionIds":[],"sectionOrders":{}},"schemaVersion":2}